UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2590
1 A RESOLUTION resolving the Senate as a Court of Impeachment and providing
2 for the adoption of the Rules of Procedure therefor.
3 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives has, during the 2026 Regular Session of
4 the General Assembly, issued Articles of Impeachment against Julie Muth Goodman,
5 Circuit Judge for the 22nd Judicial Circuit consisting of Fayette County, which
6 determined that she abused the powers of the office she holds; she defied binding
7 precedents established by the highest courts of this Commonwealth; she defied statutes
8 enacted by the General Assembly and defied rules of the Kentucky Court of Justice; and
9 she interfered with the rights and powers of the grand jury, trial court jurors, attorneys,
10 and others to perform their respective roles within the Kentucky Court of Justice; and
11 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives has appointed a committee to prosecute
12 the Articles of Impeachment before the Senate, and the chairman of that committee,
13 within five days after the impeachment was ordered, did lay the Articles before the
14 Senate; and
15 WHEREAS, the Senate does now designate the day and hour to commence hearing
16 the impeachment, and the Respondent, Julie Muth Goodman, shall be summoned by
17 precept issued by the Clerk of the Senate to appear before the Senate on that date;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
20 Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The Senate now resolves itself into a Court of Impeachment for the
22 purpose of hearing the impeachment and designates April 6, 2026, at the hour of 9 a.m.
23 EDT for a hearing, continuing day to day until concluded, and that the President of the
24 Senate and the members of the Senate or the committee appointed pursuant to Section 2
25 of this Act shall take the oath prescribed by KRS 63.050, and that the Clerk of the Senate
26 shall make proper record in the Journal of the names of all Senators who take the oath.
27 Section 2. Pursuant to Senate Rule 39A, the President of the Senate will direct
Page 1 of 10
